reports.title: Explore and brainstorm possibilities for a refactor of the Kanban board project
reports.description: DO NOT IMPLEMENT OR CHANGE ANY CODE. JUST PREPARE A BRAINSTORMING DOCUMENT IN MARKDOWN. DO NOT IMPLEMENT ANY CODE. The Kanban dashboard is unstable, the UI doesn't refresh natively without being prompted, and the service generally doesn't seem to work consistently. Let's first explore the current structure of the application, identifying the entire stack, then brainstorm some alternatives, along with light exploration of how much work is involved in a refactor for each possible upgrade in the tech stack. This app only needs to work locally, but we could also host it on Vercel and lock it behind a password. It only needs to work on desktop, though later creating a Telegram app to manage the dashboard would be nice. For now just working on Mac desktop is good. My gut says this would be more stable and consistent as a React app, but maybe the instability is a result of how we're (OpenClaw / Mac) is serving data to the dashboard? Please explain in detail, and provide alternatives. Please also include a web search for how other users are managing tasks on their OpenClaw dashboards. DO NOT IMPLEMENT OR CHANGE ANY CODE. JUST PREPARE A BRAINSTORMING DOCUMENT IN MARKDOWN. DO NOT IMPLEMENT ANY CODE.
